<div style="position:absolute;left:172.38px;top:17.34px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">LA BONTE’S TOP 100 ENGLISH CONVERSATION PATTERNS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:563.58px;top:17.22px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">6</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:231.78px;top:42.06px" class="cls_007"><span class="cls_007">TAG QUESTIONS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:69.96px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">TAG QUESTIONS</span><span class="cls_014"> are used a lot in conversation, so you need to be able to use them. This is used when you anticipate a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:82.62px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">certain YES or NO answer. Note the answers. The tag question is always the opposite. If the sentence is positive, the tag</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:95.28px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">question is negative, and vice versa.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:144.72px;top:107.88px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">She </span><span class="cls_051">went</span><span class="cls_014">, </span><span class="cls_051">didn't</span><span class="cls_014"> she?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.74px;top:107.88px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Yes, she did.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:366.21px;top:107.88px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">=</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.71px;top:107.88px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Yes, she went.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:166.80px;top:120.54px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">+</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:200.49px;top:120.54px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">-</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.75px;top:120.54px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">No, she didn't.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:366.24px;top:120.54px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">=</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.74px;top:120.54px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">No, she didn't go.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:144.72px;top:133.20px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">She </span><span class="cls_051">didn't go</span><span class="cls_014">, </span><span class="cls_051">did</span><span class="cls_014"> she?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.75px;top:133.20px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">No, she didn't.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:366.21px;top:133.20px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">=</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.71px;top:133.20px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">No, she didn't go.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:172.26px;top:145.86px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">-</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:214.45px;top:145.86px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">+</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.73px;top:145.86px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Yes, she did.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:366.25px;top:145.86px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">=</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.73px;top:145.86px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Yes, he went.</span></div>
