<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:586.32px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">FUTURE*</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:103.96px;top:586.32px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">+ Are you going to be </span><span class="cls_051">v</span><span class="cls_015">ing?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:346.79px;top:586.32px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">He's going to be </span><span class="cls_051">v</span><span class="cls_015">ing.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.31px;top:598.98px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">- Isn't she going to be </span><span class="cls_051">v</span><span class="cls_015">ing?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:335.74px;top:598.98px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">They aren't going to be </span><span class="cls_051">v</span><span class="cls_015">ing.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:75.24px;top:611.57px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">*Instead of WILL, use </span><span class="cls_015">AM GOING TO BE </span><span class="cls_051">v</span><span class="cls_015">ING</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:86.20px;top:624.17px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Is she going to be teaching?</span></div>
