<img src="files/background039.jpg" width=612 height=792></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:172.38px;top:17.34px" class="cls_004"><span class="cls_004">LA BONTE’S TOP 100 ENGLISH CONVERSATION PATTERNS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:557.58px;top:17.22px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">30</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:174.00px;top:34.98px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">IT IS WORTH </span><span class="cls_056">v</span><span class="cls_003">ING.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:77.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  Other variations of IT IS WORTH </span><span class="cls_054">v</span><span class="cls_002">ING are:</span><span class="cls_011">   IT IS WORTHWHILE </span><span class="cls_053">v</span><span class="cls_011">ING.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.72px;top:91.80px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">IT IS WORTHWHILE TO </span><span class="cls_053">v</span><span class="cls_011">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.72px;top:105.60px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">IT IS WORTH IT TO </span><span class="cls_053">v</span><span class="cls_011">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Is it worthwhile studying that?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.72px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Yes, it's worthwhile studying that.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:133.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Isn't it worthwhile to take that class?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.71px;top:133.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">No, it isn't worthwhile to take that class.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:146.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Was it worth it to buy it then?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.78px;top:146.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">No, it wasn't worth it to buy it then.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:160.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">2.  </span><span class="cls_011">IT'S WORTH IT.</span><span class="cls_002"> You will hear this pattern sometimes used without a verb. It often refers to</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:54.73px;top:174.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">whether the price of something is too high or too low, or whether the result of something you do</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:54.72px;top:188.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">is satisfactory.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:202.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Is it worth it?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.80px;top:202.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">No, it isn't worth it.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:215.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Wasn't the trip worth it?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.76px;top:215.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">No, it wasn't worth it.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:229.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Was that watch worth it?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.73px;top:229.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Yes, that watch was worth it.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:243.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">3.  </span><span class="cls_011">IT</span><span class="cls_002"> is usually the subject, but sometimes other pronouns/nouns are used.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:257.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">That book is worth reading.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.77px;top:257.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Were they worth taking to school?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:271.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">She is worth talking to.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.68px;top:271.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Was that car worth buying?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:284.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">4.  Another variation of this pattern is:  </span><span class="cls_011">IT PAYS TO </span><span class="cls_053">v</span><span class="cls_011">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:298.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Does it pay to get that now?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.72px;top:298.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Yes, it pays to get that now.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:312.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Did it pay to buy that in advance?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.61px;top:312.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">No, it didn't pay to buy that in advance.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:326.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Did it pay to finish early?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.72px;top:326.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">Yes, it paid to finish early.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:354.00px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">PAST</span></div>
