<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:322.44px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">* </span><span class="cls_053">IN</span><span class="cls_002"> is optional.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:47.75px;top:336.36px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">1.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.51px;top:336.36px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">If you use a noun or an object pronoun, you have to use </span><span class="cls_015">IN </span><span class="cls_051">n/op/v</span><span class="cls_015">ING</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:348.95px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">There was no sense in</span><span class="cls_015"> them</span><span class="cls_014"> coming.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.67px;top:348.95px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">Is there any use in </span><span class="cls_015">me </span><span class="cls_014">helping?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:108.72px;top:361.61px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">There isn't any use in </span><span class="cls_015">the teacher </span><span class="cls_014">going.</span></div>
