<div style="position:absolute;left:261.00px;top:34.98px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">I GET </span><span class="cls_056">a</span><span class="cls_003">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:232.98px;top:62.58px" class="cls_003"><span class="cls_003">I BECOME </span><span class="cls_056">a</span><span class="cls_003">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:48.72px;top:105.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">1.  </span><span class="cls_011">MORE</span><span class="cls_002"> is often used before the adjective.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:95.22px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">She got angrier.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:189.63px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">(more angry)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.72px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">It’ll get colder.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:414.43px;top:119.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">(more cold)</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:147.00px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">PAST</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:109.63px;top:147.00px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">+  Did you become </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_011">?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.77px;top:147.00px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">She got </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_011">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:109.62px;top:160.80px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">-  Didn't she get </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_011">?</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.78px;top:160.80px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">You didn't become </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_011">.</span></div>
