<div style="position:absolute;left:124.93px;top:397.68px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">I bought </span><span class="cls_015">his</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:288.74px;top:397.68px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">THEIRS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:399.41px;top:397.68px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">Theirs</span><span class="cls_014"> was expensive.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.73px;top:410.34px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">HERS</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:124.93px;top:410.34px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">They wore </span><span class="cls_015">hers</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.73px;top:435.60px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">* With the 1st and 3rd person  plural subject pronoun</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:287.92px;top:435.60px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">and object pronoun, you can add a number after the pronoun.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:124.93px;top:448.26px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">We three</span><span class="cls_014"> ate dinner there.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.75px;top:448.26px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">He took </span><span class="cls_015">us four</span><span class="cls_014"> to the movies.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:124.92px;top:460.92px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">You two </span><span class="cls_014">should come here.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.77px;top:460.92px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">She invited </span><span class="cls_015">you five</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:473.58px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">**To make a noun into a possessive pronoun, add "'s" to the noun or person's name.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:124.92px;top:486.24px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">I took Mr. Lee</span><span class="cls_015">'s</span><span class="cls_014"> computer.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:324.72px;top:486.24px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">She took John</span><span class="cls_015">'s</span><span class="cls_014"> books.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:511.56px" class="cls_051"><span class="cls_051">PRONOUN</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:180.31px;top:511.56px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">SINGULAR</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:403.46px;top:511.56px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">PLURAL</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.72px;top:524.15px" class="cls_015"><span class="cls_015">Subject</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:125.28px;top:524.15px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">I</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:164.71px;top:524.15px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">you</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:216.71px;top:524.15px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">he</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:275.22px;top:524.15px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">she</span></div>
