<div style="position:absolute;left:322.05px;top:607.55px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">She has a lot of things </span><span class="cls_015">for them</span><span class="cls_014"> to eat.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:36.74px;top:620.21px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">6.  Instead of A LOT OF you can use </span><span class="cls_015">LOTS OF</span><span class="cls_014">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.73px;top:632.87px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">They have </span><span class="cls_015">lots of</span><span class="cls_014"> things to fix.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:274.76px;top:632.87px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">=</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:319.44px;top:632.87px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">They have a lot of things to fix.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.74px;top:645.47px" class="cls_014"><span class="cls_014">There were</span><span class="cls_015"> lots of</span><span class="cls_014"> people at the picnic.</span></div>
