<div style="position:absolute;left:260.52px;top:253.32px" class="cls_058"><span class="cls_058">ADJECTIVE</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:54.72px;top:288.12px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">SOMETHING </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:216.72px;top:288.12px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">SOMEBODY </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.72px;top:288.12px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">SOMEWHERE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:54.72px;top:301.92px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">ANYTHING </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:216.72px;top:301.92px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">SOMEONE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.72px;top:301.92px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">SOMEPLACE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:216.72px;top:315.72px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">ANYBODY </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.72px;top:315.72px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">ANYPLACE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:216.72px;top:329.58px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">ANYONE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:396.72px;top:329.58px" class="cls_011"><span class="cls_011">ANYWHERE </span><span class="cls_053">a</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:42.71px;top:349.08px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">- You can add THAT IS or WHICH IS before the </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_002"> with any combination of SOMETHING/ANYTHING</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:54.72px;top:362.88px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">and SOMEWHERE/ANYWHERE.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:42.72px;top:376.68px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">- You can add WHO IS or THAT IS before the </span><span class="cls_053">a</span><span class="cls_002"> with any combination of SOMEONE/ANYONE.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:42.72px;top:390.48px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">- The tense of the verb TO BE usually takes the same tense of the verb preceding SOMEWHERE etc.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:72.72px;top:404.28px" class="cls_002"><span class="cls_002">I met someone beautiful.</span></div>
