<div style="position:absolute;left:36.70px;top:695.47px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">3.  </span><span class="cls_005">PERSON'S NAME</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:153.71px;top:695.46px" class="cls_005"><span class="cls_005">JIM WHO  s</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.74px;top:706.98px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">You can use a person's name here with either the verb or adjective.  You have to use </span><span class="cls_005">WHO</span><span class="cls_012">. Do not use THE in front of</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:56.76px;top:718.45px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">the person's name.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:95.22px;top:729.97px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">He swam with </span><span class="cls_005">John who he lives with</span><span class="cls_012">.</span></div>
<div style="position:absolute;left:95.22px;top:741.49px" class="cls_012"><span class="cls_012">I introduced her to </span><span class="cls_005">Carol who I met in high school</span><span class="cls_012">.</span></div>
